<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2993a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-25T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 25,
                                            1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>British Embassy states it has received instructions to ask us to join
                                in requesting the Chinese Government to remove military Governor
                                [of] Shensi responsible for breach of Armistice. Is this covered by
                                your telegrams March 7, 1 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d328fn39"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_316">p.
                                    316</ref>.</note> and March 13, 4 p.m. and the Department’s
                                instructions of March 14, 4 p.m. If not what do you think of this
                                proposal?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>